    <section class="beach">
      <h2>1.MARINE DRIVE</h2>
      <img
        src="Images\marine-marine-drive-mumbai-mumbai-sea-872904.jpg"
        alt="Juhu Beach"
        class="beach-img"
      />
      <p class="paragraph">
        This iconic avenue, which runs alongside the Arabian Sea, is a popular
        site for watching sunsets and is particularly beautiful when lit up at
        night. Marine Drive is a three-kilometer-long promenade in Mumbai that
        runs parallel to the NSB road. After dusk, you can go to either end of
        Marine Drive and see the lights shining in a beautiful arc all along the
        coast, which is hidden by palm trees. People come here to walk in the
        evenings to see the spectacular sunset. It's also one of the spots where
        people go late at night, with vendors selling chai and cigarettes at all
        hours of the day and night. A picture of the Mumbai skyline, the sound
        of the waves
      </p>
      <div class="details">
        <strong>Location:</strong>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/M6Mi5q7SPeDox38FA"
          >Marine lines, South Mumbai</a
        ><br />
