        Nearby bus stop - Marine lines beach bus stop<br />
        <strong>Entry Fee:</strong> No Entry Fee<br />
        <strong>Nearby visiting places:</strong>Wankhede stadium, Taraporwala
        aquarium, Girgaumn Chowpatty, Brabourn stadium
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="beach">
      <h2>2. Gateway of India</h2>
      <img
        src="Images\gateway of india.jpg"
        alt="Aksa Beach"
        class="beach-img"
      />
      <p class="paragraph">
        The Gateway of India, located near Apollo Bunder in South Mumbai, on the
        Arabian Sea's beach, is India's most unique monument. The structural
        construction of the Gateway of India is built on a gigantic arch. The
        monument is composed of yellow basalt and indissoluble concrete. The
        structural plan of the Gateway of India is designed in the
        Indo-Saracenic style. There are also remains of Muslim architectural
        styles in the massive monument's structure. The four turrets are the
        most prominent features of the Gateway of India's overall design. Behind
        the Gateway's arch, which leads to the Arabian Sea, there are steps
        built. The monument is constructed so that visitors may instantly
        observe the vast length of the 'blue blanket,' which is both welcome and
        comforting.
      </p>
      <div class="details">
        <strong>Location:</strong>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/BHsgM8n1Hkpt317n7"
          >Apollo Bandar, Colaba, Mumbai</a
        ><br />
        <strong>How to Reach:</strong> Nearby Railway Station - churchgate
        Station<br />
        <strong>Nearby Bus Stop:</strong>Gateway of India<br />
        <strong>Entry Fee:</strong> No Entry Fee<br />
        <strong>Nearby Visiting Places:</strong> Taj mahal palace hotel, Arabian
        sea, Oberoi hotel, CSM Vastu Sangrahalay <br />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="beach">
      <h2>3. Bandra worli sea link</h2>
      <img
        src="Images\Bandra-Worli-Sea-Link-Night-View.jpg"
        alt="Madh Island Beach"
        class="beach-img"
      />
      <p class="paragraph">
        This is a bridge which links Mumbai’s suburbs to South Mumbai.  It is a
        cable bridge that connects Bandra in Mumbai's west to Worli in Mumbai's
        south. Passengers travelling from Bandra to Worli and vice versa might
        save a significant amount of time thanks to this bridge. On either side
        of the bridge, concrete steel viaducts provide support. This Mumbai
        bridge is an excellent example of the authorities' excellent engineering
        achievement. It is regarded as one of Mumbai's most unique areas, where
        you may take a long drive with your loved ones while viewing the city's
        stunning skyline and the majestic sea flowing beneath you.
      </p>
      <div class="details">
        <strong>Location:</strong>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/6r2wXbiRcUPG22Td9"
          > Bandra in the Western Suburbs of Mumbai with Worli in South Mumbai.  </a
        ><br />
        <strong>How to reach:</strong> Nearby railway station - Bandra<br />
        <strong>Nearby Bus stop:</strong> Bandra worli sea link <br />
        <strong>Entry Fee:</strong> ₹85 (US$1.10) Car ₹110 (US$1.40) LCV
        ₹145 (US$1.90) Heavy vehicle<br />
        <strong>Nearby visiting Place:</strong> Pali hills, Bandra Bandstand,
        linking road, BKC, Mount Mary church, Galaxy Apartment, Mannat.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="beach">
      <h2>4.Taj mahal palace hotel:</h2>
      <img
        src="Images\taj mahal hotel.jpg"
        alt="Marve Beach"
        class="beach-img"
      />
      <p class="paragraph">
        The Taj Mahal Palace, which was built in 1903 and overlooks the Arabian
        Sea, rises magnificently opposite the Gateway of India. It's spread out
        over 2.6 acres. The decor and architecture are inspired by Indian
        culture. This iconic luxury hotel has hosted kings, statesmen, and
        eminent people from all over the world, and is widely regarded as a
        global leader in hospitality. The Taj Mahal Palace is strategically
        placed in Mumbai's primary historical and economic hub, just a short
        walk from Colaba Causeway, which is noted for its touristic little
        roadside stores.
      </p>
      <div class="details">
        <strong>Location:</strong>
        <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/BHsgM8n1Hkpt317n7">
          Apollo Bandar, Colaba, Mumbai </a
        ><br />
        <strong>How to reach:</strong> Nearby railway station - churchgate
        <br />
        <strong>Nearby Bus stop:</strong> Gateway of India<br />
        <strong>Entry Fee:</strong> No Fees (Outside of the hotel)<br />
        <strong>Nearby visiting Place:</strong> Gateway of India, Arabian sea,
        Oberoi hotel, CSM Vastu Sangrahalay.
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="beach">
      <h2>5. Nariman point:-</h2>
      <img
        src="Images\nariman-point-mumbai.jpg"
        alt="Girgaon Chowpatty"
        class="beach-img"
      />
      <p class="paragraph">
        The fourth most expensive office site in the world is Nariman Point. It
        is home to some of the country's most prestigious financial and business
        institutions, including Air India, the Central Bank of India, the Indian
        Express, the State Bank of India, and the Oberoi Hotel, among others. It
        is one of Mumbai's upscale locations, located on the extreme southern
        gradient of Marine Drive. The vibrant city of Mumbai actively promotes
        this location as a major tourist destination. The stunning view of the
        Arabian Sea, which is the highlight of Nariman Point and attracts
        tourists from all over the country and the world, is even more
        impressive. Furthermore, because to the presence of exceptional star
        hotels, pubs, and clubs, Nariman Point's nightlife is highly vibrant.
      </p>
      <div class="details">
        <strong>Location:</strong>
